//Lateral collateral ligaments


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 - Ligaments, joint capsule & menisci of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Lateral collateral ligaments' from the Finding dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Sprain, grade 1 Injury' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial tear, grade 2 injury' radio button is enabled
And 'Complete tear, grade 3 injury' radio button is enabled
And 'Avulsion fracture' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Partial tear, grade 2 injury' radio button
Then 'Lateral collateral ligament' checkbox is enabled
And 'Iliotibial band' checkbox is enabled
And 'Biceps femoris tendon' checkbox is enabled
And 'Popliteofibular ligament' checkbox is enabled
And 'Meniscopopliteal ligament' checkbox is enabled

And 'Proximal' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal' radio button is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Retraction' checkbox
Then 'Dimension in mm' input field is enabled

When I select 'Complete tear, grade 3 injury' radio button
Then 'Proximal' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal' radio button is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Retraction' checkbox
Then 'Dimension in mm' input field is enabled


When I select 'Avulsion fracture' radio button
Then 'Segond fracture' checkbox is enabled
And 'Arcuate sign' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Segond fracture' checkbox
Then 'Avulsion Tibia' checkbox is enabled
And 'Rupture of the anterior cruciate ligament' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Arcuate sign' checkbox
Then 'Avulsion fracture proximal fibula' checkbox is enabled
And 'Avulsion of the posterolateral capsule' checkbox is enabled
And 'Rupture of the posterior cruciate ligament' checkbox is enabled
